			<pubDate>Sun, 20 Jul 2008 15:46:02 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[A couple of video's of death knight gameplay.  Having watched them, I can say it is amazing what the current capabilities of the death knight are.  In two of the videos, the only downtime that is taken is the time to find another monster to kill.  It's incredible what the death knight can...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>A couple of video's of death knight gameplay.  Having watched them, I can say it is amazing what the current capabilities of the death knight are.  In two of the videos, the only downtime that is taken is the time to find another monster to kill.  It's incredible what the death knight can accomplish.  I definitely see some number adjustment going on to various Death Knight abilities and talents, as I doubt Blizzard wanted them as powerful as they appear in these videos.  If they did, well, I shudder at the thought of facing one in PvP.<br />
<br />
The videos include 2 instances of Blood spec non-stop grinding, one of AoE grinding involving corpse explosion and death and decay (which looks amazing, I might add), and one demonstrating the control and burst capabilities of Frost (the jaw dropping part happening within the first minute).<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.vimeo.com/user615417/videos" target="_blank">http://www.vimeo.com/user615417/videos</a><br />
<br />
Some random thoughts:<br />
-Death and Decay looks to complement paladin AE tanking incredibly well.<br />
-Death and Decay will probably get adjusted to be a channeling spell<br />
-The range of on the pull mob-taunt ability will probably be decreased<br />
-Blood Worms will probably either have their chance to spawn reduced or have their health restored reduced<br />
-The ghoul is sweet<br />
-The visual effects of Death Knight spells are incredibly well done.  I hope this mean other classes' spells might get an overhaul in the future.<br />
-Death's Gate looks amazing in particular<br />
-Corpse Explosion grinding, while looking impressive, is probably only feasible when you have a couple of mobs with real low HP (as the little slimes in the video did)<br />
-A skilled player behind a death knight is a force to be reckoned with</div>

]]></content:encoded>
