			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Short version:<br />
Old school action movie but nothing revolutionary, cheap tickets or rent it.<br />
<br />
Long version:<br />
I'm a huge fan of the card game of MC, the back story is very interesting esp. if you look at the factions etc. Hence when I heard that a movie was coming out I was dreading the outcome, MC is not exactly a PC world, you got demons, heretics, demonic temples while greed is good and evil walks on earth. How could you ever make a movie out of this?<br />
<br />
Well as it turns out you can't really. The story is focused on earth and you don't get to see a whole lot of the actual five corporations (well considering the time it would actually been four) or how they interact. The start up scene gives an idea at least though. The world it is playing out in is a WW2 with steam tech kind of set up yet they do have modern weapons as well but not modern tanks etc. for the troops (costs to much).<br />
<br />
The story is straight forward enough an ancient enemy is let lose on earth and only our gang of heroes can save us (ever heard that one before?). The story becomes a bit more interesting (though not a whole lot) when the ancient enemy starts to show how it is created etc. but nothing major. One of the things which surprised me though was how bloody it was yet not going over the top. Also it surprised me slightly in how it played out in terms of main character development.<br />
<br />
Still I'd have to say I recommend it, it is a interesting movie but not a masterpiece one. Get good price on the tickets or rent it and watch it in complete darkness,</div>

]]></content:encoded>
