			<pubDate>Sun, 20 Jul 2008 14:34:29 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[As much as I like a pritine aquarium - super clean, sparkling water - I've decided that algae is a good thing.  After thinking about Koi ponds, and the amount of slime that is allowed to grow - I decided NOT to scrape the algae off the back wall of my aquarium.  It has turned into a brown green mat...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>As much as I like a pritine aquarium - super clean, sparkling water - I've decided that algae is a good thing.  After thinking about Koi ponds, and the amount of slime that is allowed to grow - I decided NOT to scrape the algae off the back wall of my aquarium.  It has turned into a brown green mat of something awful, but somehow doesn't look all that bad against a black background.<br />
<br />
But the interesting thing is how much this has improved my water quality.  It used to be that weekly water changes were a must - but now, my tank can go a whole month between water changes.  My fish (one large goldfish in a 30 gallon tank) is much more energetic, and seems to be doing much better health wise.  His fins were rather beat up - but they are improving dramatically, I believe because the of the water quality improvements.<br />
<br />
Lesson learned I guess - sometimes there is such a thing as too clean...<br />
<br />
What do you all do with algae in your tank?  Eliminate or allow?</div>

]]></content:encoded>
