			<title>Movies Starship Troopers 3 - The horror continues</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=59382&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sun, 20 Jul 2008 14:29:06 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Short version: 
Only rent if you are a desperate Starship Trooper fan and got half a bottle of scotch to down before seeing it (the other half will be used afterwards trying to forget it had the ST name on it).  
 
Long version: 
I'm a Starship Trooper fan, I'll admit it straight up. I've read the...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Short version:<br />
Only rent if you are a desperate Starship Trooper fan and got half a bottle of scotch to down before seeing it (the other half will be used afterwards trying to forget it had the ST name on it). <br />
<br />
Long version:<br />
I'm a Starship Trooper fan, I'll admit it straight up. I've read the book and still did not go into a frenzy over how the movie did not follow the book. I saw it for what it was, I laughed and enjoyed it greatly.<br />
<br />
I saw ST2, I flinched at the new computer models, I tried to find some reason not to send a bill to Hollywood for the wasted time. There was one or two moments which was worth watching.<br />
<br />
I enjoyed the cartoon version, well done, story was predictable but hey, take it for it was.<br />
<br />
And now I saw ST3 was due to come out and that it was to be &quot;closer to the original&quot; I had some very minor hopes it would not be a Episode 1 - 3 fiasco. Ok, they have remodelled the bugs again fine. They added another three new once for dubious reasons in case of at least one but I'd argue two but ok, I can live with that. They went back to the TV commercial set up and tried to bring it back to ST1, I can dig that. <br />
<br />
But who in the seven hells was paid to write this story because a three year old with a crayon could have done better!!! I was hoping for something more along the lines of Mutant Chronicles (decently done I have to say though the end was, well, stupid) where there was a bit of darkness in the story. I wanted steroid pumped, barb wire chewing, gasoline pissing sergeants with nukes taking on legions; not a bunch of fat guys with tied shoe laces tumbling around trying to figure out which end of the gun to point towards the enemy! I wanted to see new all improved weapons of mass destruction not have the machine guns suddenly downgraded to water guns with out water.<br />
<br />
The only saving grace comes in the name of the movie, the marauders, and only because I'm a desperate fan of what they are (don't want to spoiler that part). Sadly the marauders are in there for a minute or so in total and that is it. The only other saving grace is the song (you'll know which one once you've seen it) I guess but only if you got black humour.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
